idn2_free(3)                                                             libidn2                                                            idn2_free(3)

NAME
       idn2_free - API function

SYNOPSIS
       #include <idn2.h>

       void idn2_free(void * ptr);

ARGUMENTS
       void * ptr  pointer to deallocate

DESCRIPTION
       Call free(3) on the given pointer.

       This  function  is typically only useful on systems where the library malloc heap is different from the library caller malloc heap, which happens
       on Windows when the library is a separate DLL.

